<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-21T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-21T01:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4346: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-21T14:00:00+08:00">February 21, 1932—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 21—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>94. Referring to my telegram No. 90, February 20, 6 p.m., paragraph 3,
                            regarding protest by Senior Consul on February 20th against use by
                            Japanese forces of International Settlement as a base or channel of
                            military operations. This action by consular body was proposed by French
                            Consul General as a result of my conversations with him under
                            Department’s 22, February 13, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Not repeated to the Legation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CES1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>